{"name": "drb-driver-json", "metadata": {"name": "drb-driver-json", "version": "1.3.0", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Plugins", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Lesser General Public License v3 (LGPLv3)", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "home_page": "", "license": "LGPLv3", "documentation_url": "https://drb-python.gitlab.io/impl/json", "dependencies": ["drb"], "summary": "DRB json driver", "upload_time": 1694695722}, "documentation": ["# JsonNode Implementation\n\nThis `drb-driver-json` module implements json format access with DRB data\nmodel. It is able to navigates among the json contents.\n\n## Json Factory and Json Node\n\nThe module implements the basic factory model defined in DRB in its node\nresolver. Based on the python entry point mechanism, this module can be\ndynamically imported into applications.\n\nThe entry point group reference is `drb.driver`.<br/>\nThe driver name is `json`.<br/>\nThe factory class `JsonNodeFactory` is encoded into `drb.drivers.json.factory`.\n\n\nThe json factory creates a JsonNode from an existing json content. It uses a\nbase node to access the content data using the streamed base node\nimplementation.\n\nThe base node can be a FileNode (See drb), HttpNode, ZipNode or\nany other node able to provide streamed (`BufferedIOBase`, `RawIOBase`, `IO`)\njson content.\n\n## limitations\n\nThe current version does not manage child modification and insertion. JsonNode\nis currently read only.\n\n## Using this module\n\nTo include this module into your project, the `drb-driver-json` module shall be\nreferenced into `requirement.txt` file, or the following pip line can be run:\n\n```commandline\npip install drb-driver-json\n```\n\n### Node Creation:\n\nThe driver can create a JsonNode by giving the path to a json file:\n\n```\nfrom drb.drivers.json import DrbJsonNode\n\nnode = JsonNode(PATH_JSON)\n```\n\nthe driver can also give a dictionary in argument:\n\n```\nfrom drb.drivers.json import DrbJsonNode\n\nDICT = { \n        \"id\":\"01\", \n        \"name\": \"Tom\", \n        \"lastname\": \"Price\" \n     }\nnode = JsonNode(NAME_OF_YOUR_NODE, data = DICT)\n```\n\nIf the baseNode is an HttpNode, FileNode... the driver can retrieve the data of\nyour Json with this:\n\n ```\nfrom drb.drivers.json import JsonNodeFactory\n\nFACTORY = JsonNodeFactory()\nFILE_NODE = DrbFileNode(PATH_TO_YOUR_JSON)\nNODE = FACTORY.create(FILE_NODE)\n```\n\n### Different types of data\n\n| data          | JSON Type | Python Type |\n|:--------------|:----------|:------------|\n| null          | null      | None        |\n| true/false    | boolean   | bool        |\n| 'hello World' | string    | str         |\n| 1             | int       | int         |\n| 1.0           | number    | float       |\n| [...]         | array     | list        |\n| {...}         | object    | dict        |\n\n### Documentation\n\nThe documentation of this driver can be found here\nhttps://drb-python.gitlab.io/impl/json\n"], "modules": [{"name": "drb.topics.json", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "drb.drivers.json.factory", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "drb.drivers.json.factory.JsonNodeFactory", "bases": ["DrbFactory"], "methods": [{"name": "drb.drivers.json.factory.JsonNodeFactory._create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "node", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "DrbNode", "xref": {"fqname": "drb.core.node.DrbNode", "project": "drb"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "DrbNode", "xref": {"fqname": "drb.core.node.DrbNode", "project": "drb"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The JsonNodeFactory class allow us to build drb nodes according\n to the form of the json you want to read.\nAfter this class is created you can call the _create method\n with the drb node created from the\npath of the Json file you want to read"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "drb.drivers.json", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "drb.drivers.json.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "drb.drivers.json.JsonBaseNode", "xref": {"fqname": "drb.drivers.json.node.JsonBaseNode", "project": null}}, {"name": "drb.drivers.json.JsonNode", "xref": {"fqname": "drb.drivers.json.node.JsonNode", "project": null}}, {"name": "drb.drivers.json.JsonNodeFactory", "xref": {"fqname": "drb.drivers.json.factory.JsonNodeFactory", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "drb.drivers.json._version", "documentation": ["This file was generated by 'versioneer.py' (0.29) from", "revision-control system data, or from the parent directory name of an", "unpacked source archive. Distribution tarballs contain a pre-generated copy", "of this file."], "functions": [{"name": "drb.drivers.json._version.get_versions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "drb.drivers.json._version.version_json", "type": null, "documentation": ["END VERSION_JSON"]}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "drb.drivers.json.node", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "drb.drivers.json.node._to_dict", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "node", "type": {"name": "JsonNode", "xref": {"fqname": "drb.drivers.json.node.JsonNode", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "drb.drivers.json.node._to_list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "node", "type": {"name": "JsonNode", "xref": {"fqname": "drb.driver